# .gitleaksignore — suppress gitleaks false positives
#
# cdk.out/ is already in .gitignore so it won't appear in git history.
# If gitleaks is run against the working tree (e.g. pre-commit) and finds
# false positives in synthesised CloudFormation assets, add their SHA256
# fingerprints below (one per line).
#
# Generate a fingerprint for a specific finding:
#   gitleaks detect --report-format json | jq '.[].Fingerprint'
#
# Example:
#   a1b2c3d4e5f6...
